import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Load the data from the CSV file
file_path = r'C:\Users\hayae\Downloads\sample_data\sample_1.csv'
#file_path = r'C:\Users\hayae\Downloads\sample_data\sample_2.csv'
df = pd.read_csv(file_path)

df['startTimestamp'] = pd.to_datetime(df['startTimestamp'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')

fig, ax1 = plt.subplots(figsize=(30, 15))

# Plot Heart Rate 
heart_rate_data = df[df['Type'] == 'HeartRate']
ax1.plot(heart_rate_data['startTimestamp'], heart_rate_data['Long Value'], label='HeartRate', marker='o', color='#1f77b4')
ax1.set_xlabel('Time', size=20, fontweight='bold')
ax1.set_ylabel('Heart Rate (bpm)', size=20, fontweight='bold', color='#1f77b4')
ax1.tick_params(axis='y', labelsize=14, colors='#1f77b4')
ax1.tick_params(axis='x', labelsize=14)
ax1.legend(loc='upper left', fontsize=14)
ax1.grid(True)

# Create a secondary y-axis to plot Steps
ax2 = ax1.twinx()
steps_data = df[df['Type'] == 'Steps']
ax2.plot(steps_data['startTimestamp'], steps_data['Double Value'], label='Steps', marker='o', color='g')
ax2.set_ylabel('Steps', size=20, fontweight='bold', color='g')
ax2.tick_params(axis='y', labelsize=14, colors='g')
ax2.legend(loc='upper right', fontsize=14)

plt.title('Heart Rate and Steps Over Time - Sample 1', size=30, fontweight='bold')

# Formatting x-axis labels
fig.autofmt_xdate()  

plt.savefig(r'C:\Users\hayae\Downloads\sample_data\Plots\heart_rate_steps_combined.png')
plt.show()

Plot Showing the Correlation just between Heart Rate and Step

In [212]:
#One plot showing the correlation just between heart rate and steps. Also shows Pearson's correlation and regression line with probability interval (red)

import warnings
from warnings import simplefilter

# Ignore all future warnings
simplefilter(action='ignore', category=FutureWarning)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
from scipy.stats import pearsonr


file_path = r'C:\Users\hayae\Downloads\sample_data\sample_1.csv'
#file_path = r'C:\Users\hayae\Downloads\sample_data\sample_2.csv'
df = pd.read_csv(file_path)

df['startTimestamp'] = pd.to_datetime(df['startTimestamp'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')

# Filter data for Heart Rate and Steps
heart_rate_data = df[df['Type'] == 'HeartRate'][['startTimestamp', 'Long Value']]
steps_data = df[df['Type'] == 'Steps'][['startTimestamp', 'Double Value']]


merged_data = pd.merge(heart_rate_data, steps_data, on='startTimestamp', how='inner')
merged_data.columns = ['startTimestamp', 'HeartRate', 'Steps']

# Calculate Pearson correlation coefficient
correlation, _ = pearsonr(merged_data['HeartRate'], merged_data['Steps'])

plt.figure(figsize=(15, 10))
sns.scatterplot(x='HeartRate', y='Steps', data=merged_data, s=100, color='b', label='Data Points')
sns.regplot(x='HeartRate', y='Steps', data=merged_data, scatter=False, color='r', label='Regression Line')
plt.xlabel('Heart Rate (bpm)', size=20, fontweight='bold')
plt.ylabel('Steps', size=20, fontweight='bold')
plt.title(f'Correlation between Heart Rate and Steps', size=24, fontweight='bold')
plt.xticks(fontsize=14)
plt.yticks(fontsize=14)
plt.grid(True)

plt.legend(title=f'Pearson Correlation: {correlation:.2f}', fontsize=14)

plt.savefig(r'C:\Users\hayae\Downloads\sample_data\Plots\correlation_heart_rate_steps_log.png')

plt.show()

Correlation Matrix with Density plots and Histograms

In [220]:
#Correlation Matrix

import warnings
from warnings import simplefilter

simplefilter(action='ignore', category=FutureWarning)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
from scipy.stats import pearsonr
import numpy as np
    
file_path = r'C:\Users\hayae\Downloads\sample_data\sample_2.csv'
df = pd.read_csv(file_path)
    
df['startTimestamp'] = pd.to_datetime(df['startTimestamp'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')
    
# Filter and combine relevant data
heart_rate_data = df[df['Type'] == 'HeartRate'][['startTimestamp', 'Long Value']].rename(columns={'Long Value': 'HeartRate'})
steps_data = df[df['Type'] == 'Steps'][['startTimestamp', 'Double Value']].rename(columns={'Double Value': 'Steps'})
calories_data = df[df['Type'] == 'ActiveBurnedCalories'][['startTimestamp', 'Double Value']].rename(columns={'Double Value': 'ActiveBurnedCalories'})
    
combined_data = heart_rate_data.merge(steps_data, on='startTimestamp', how='outer')
combined_data = combined_data.merge(calories_data, on='startTimestamp', how='outer')
    
# Drop missing values
combined_data.dropna(inplace=True)
    
# Check if combined_data is not empty
if combined_data.empty:
    print("Combined data is empty after merging and dropping NAs.")
else:
    print("Combined data has been successfully prepared.")
    
# Function to calculate correlation coefficients
def corrfunc(x, y, **kws):
    if len(x) > 1 and len(y) > 1:
        r, _ = pearsonr(x, y)
        ax = plt.gca()
        ax.annotate(f'{r:.2f}', xy=(.5, .9), xycoords=ax.transAxes, ha='center', va='center', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
    
# Plotting the pairplot
g = sns.pairplot(combined_data, diag_kind='kde')
    
    
g = sns.PairGrid(combined_data)
g.map_upper(corrfunc)
g.map_lower(sns.scatterplot)
g.map_diag(sns.histplot, kde_kws={'lw': 3})
    
plt.suptitle('Correlation Matrix', size=24, fontweight='bold')
plt.subplots_adjust(top=0.95)
    
    
plt.savefig(r'C:\Users\hayae\Downloads\sample_data\Plots\correlation_matrix_simple.png')
plt.show()

Combined data has been successfully prepared.

import warnings
from warnings import simplefilter

simplefilter(action='ignore', category=FutureWarning)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
from scipy.stats import pearsonr
import numpy as np


file_path = r'C:\Users\hayae\Downloads\sample_data\sample_1.csv'
df = pd.read_csv(file_path)

df['startTimestamp'] = pd.to_datetime(df['startTimestamp'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')

heart_rate_data = df[df['Type'] == 'HeartRate'][['startTimestamp', 'Long Value']].rename(columns={'Long Value': 'HeartRate'})
steps_data = df[df['Type'] == 'Steps'][['startTimestamp', 'Double Value']].rename(columns={'Double Value': 'Steps'})
calories_data = df[df['Type'] == 'ActiveBurnedCalories'][['startTimestamp', 'Double Value']].rename(columns={'Double Value': 'ActiveBurnedCalories'})

combined_data = heart_rate_data.merge(steps_data, on='startTimestamp', how='outer')
combined_data = combined_data.merge(calories_data, on='startTimestamp', how='outer')

combined_data.dropna(inplace=True)

if combined_data.empty:
    print("Combined data is empty after merging and dropping NAs.")
else:
    print("Combined data has been successfully prepared.")

# Calculate the p-values for each pair of numerical columns
numerical_cols = combined_data.select_dtypes(include=['float64', 'int64']).columns
p_values = pd.DataFrame(index=numerical_cols, columns=numerical_cols)

for col1, col2 in itertools.combinations(numerical_cols, 2):
    if combined_data[col1].isnull().all() or combined_data[col2].isnull().all():
        p_value = None
    else:
        # Calculate the Pearson correlation coefficient and the p-value
        _, p_value = pearsonr(combined_data[col1], combined_data[col2])
    
    p_values.loc[col1, col2] = p_value
    p_values.loc[col2, col1] = p_value

# Print the p-values
for col1, col2 in itertools.combinations(numerical_cols, 2):
    print(f"P-value for {col1} and {col2}: {p_values.loc[col1, col2]}")

# Plot the correlation matrix
def corrfunc(x, y, **kws):
    if len(x) > 1 and len(y) > 1:
        r, _ = pearsonr(x, y)
        ax = plt.gca()
        ax.annotate(f'{r:.2f}', xy=(.5, .9), xycoords=ax.transAxes, ha='center', va='center', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')

g = sns.PairGrid(combined_data)

# correlation function to the upper triangle
g.map_upper(corrfunc)

# regression plot with a single colour to the lower triangle
g.map_lower(sns.regplot, scatter_kws={'s': 20}, line_kws={'color': 'red'})

# histogram to the diagonal
g.map_diag(sns.histplot, kde_kws={'lw': 3})

plt.suptitle('Correlation Matrix - Sample 1', size=24, fontweight='bold')

plt.subplots_adjust(top=0.9) 

plt.savefig(r'C:\Users\hayae\Downloads\sample_data\Plots\correlation_matrix_colored.png')
plt.show()

Combined data has been successfully prepared.
P-value for HeartRate and Steps: 0.0034113637402812765
P-value for HeartRate and ActiveBurnedCalories: 5.958366302175389e-06
P-value for Steps and ActiveBurnedCalories: 7.207547111985528e-69

Violin Plot comparing Sleep State Against Heart Rate

In [216]:
import warnings
from warnings import simplefilter


simplefilter(action='ignore', category=FutureWarning)


import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
from scipy.stats import spearmanr

#file_path = r'C:\Users\hayae\Downloads\sample_data\sample_1.csv'
file_path = r'C:\Users\hayae\Downloads\sample_data\sample_2.csv'
df = pd.read_csv(file_path)


df['startTimestamp'] = pd.to_datetime(df['startTimestamp'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')

# Initialize 
results = []

# Iterate through the DataFrame
for i in range(1, len(df)):
    if df.iloc[i]['Type'] == 'SleepStateBinary' and df.iloc[i]['Boolean Value'] == 'yes':
        # If the current row is 'yes' in SleepStateBinary, take the 'Long Value' from the row above
        if df.iloc[i-1]['Type'] == 'HeartRate':
            results.append({'SleepStateBinary': 1, 'HeartRate': df.iloc[i-1]['Long Value']})
    elif df.iloc[i]['Type'] == 'HeartRate':
        # If the current row is a HeartRate measurement with no SleepStateBinary, treat it as 'no'
        results.append({'SleepStateBinary': 0, 'HeartRate': df.iloc[i]['Long Value']})

results_df = pd.DataFrame(results)

# Spearman correlation
spearman_corr, p_value = spearmanr(results_df['SleepStateBinary'], results_df['HeartRate'])
print(f'Spearman Correlation: {spearman_corr}, p-value: {p_value}')

plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
sns.violinplot(x='SleepStateBinary', y='HeartRate', data=results_df, inner=None)
plt.axhline(75, color='r', linestyle='--', label='Average resting BPM')  
plt.axhspan(185, results_df['HeartRate'].max(), color='red', alpha=0.3, label='Red Zone (≥ 185 BPM)')  
plt.axhspan(0, 40, color='yellow', alpha=0.3, label='Dangerous Low Zone (≤ 40 BPM)') 
plt.xlabel('Sleep State', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
plt.ylabel('Heart Rate (bpm)', fontsize=14, fontweight='bold')
plt.title('Heart Rate by Sleep State - Sample 2', fontsize=16, fontweight='bold')
plt.legend(loc='upper right') 
plt.grid(True)


plt.savefig(r'C:\Users\hayae\Downloads\sample_data\Plots\violin_plot_sleepstate_heart_rate_sample2.png')
plt.show()

Spearman Correlation: -0.11324025049296053, p-value: 9.592169156981076e-37
